<section class="faq-9 faq section light-background" id="faq">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">

            <div class="col-lg-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                <h2 class="faq-title">Have questions about university admission?</h2>
                <p class="faq-description">Find answers to common questions about university selection, admission requirements, and application processes in Kuwait.</p>
                <div class="faq-arrow d-none d-lg-block" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
                    <!-- Keep the existing SVG arrow -->
                    <svg class="faq-arrow" width="200" height="211" viewBox="0 0 200 211" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                        <!-- Keep existing path data -->
                    </svg>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-7" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300">
                <div class="faq-container">

                    <div class="faq-item faq-active">
                        <h3>How do I start my university application process?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Start by creating an account on UniSelector. You can then browse universities, check admission requirements, and submit your applications through our platform. Make sure to prepare your high school transcripts and other required documents.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>What are the general admission requirements for Kuwait universities?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Common requirements include a high school diploma with a minimum GPA, English language proficiency test scores (IELTS/TOEFL), and sometimes specific subject requirements depending on your chosen program. Each university may have additional specific requirements.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>How much are the typical university fees in Kuwait?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Fees vary significantly between public and private universities. Public universities like Kuwait University have minimal fees for Kuwaiti citizens, while private universities' fees range from 4,000 to 25,000 KWD per year depending on the program.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>When should I apply for university admission?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Most universities in Kuwait have two main intake periods: Fall (September) and Spring (January/February). It's recommended to start your application at least 3-6 months before your intended start date to ensure you meet all deadlines.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
